            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Modern Illumina-like high-throughput sequencing machines allow the cheap decoding of great amounts of DNA. The GEnomic Multi-tool (GEM) mapper is one of the fastest and most sensitive methods known to date to align such data to a known genomic reference. This unit explains how to use it effectively.",
